# CLAUDE.md — Harness Engineering Bootstrap

**Read `AGENTS.md` fully before any work.** It is your control panel.

## Mandatory Workflow

1. **Before any code change**: determine risk level (Low / Medium / High per `AGENTS.md`)
2. **Medium+ risk**: create an ExecPlan first via `/harness.plan`. Do NOT write code until plan is approved.
3. **After every change**: run `make smoke` (quick sanity) or `make check` (full suite)
4. **Before PR**: run `make review` — do not open PR if it fails

## Available Slash Commands

| Command | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| `/harness.plan` | Create an ExecPlan for medium/high risk tasks |
| `/harness.smoke` | Quick sanity check (~5s) |
| `/harness.test` | Full test suite (lint + structural) |
| `/harness.review` | Pre-PR gate (all checks) |
| `/harness.entropy` | Detect orphan scripts, broken refs |

## Key Rules

- **No code without a plan** for medium/high risk work
- **Small steps** — implement one thing, run `make smoke`, repeat
- **Verify without human** — every feature needs a deterministic, executable verification strategy
- **Log your activity** — append to `docs/activity-log.md` (files read, scripts run, decisions)
- **Update docs** when changing code — check `policies/risk-policy.json` → `docsDriftRules`
- Read `ARCHITECTURE.md` before touching project structure
- Read skill docs in `.claude/skills/harness.*/SKILL.md` for methodology details
- **Naming**: files=kebab-case, classes=PascalCase, functions/variables=snake_case
